<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 11:02AM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Cabarrus, Catawba,
Davie, Alexander, Lincoln, Iredell, Mecklenburg, Cleveland, Rowan,
Gaston and Union Counties through 1145 AM EDT...
At 1102 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 4 miles southeast of Wilkesboro to 5 miles west
of Shelby. Movement was southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Gastonia, Uptown Charlotte, Huntersville, Kannapolis, Hickory,
Downtown Concord, Monroe, Salisbury, Statesville and Shelby.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
